# Aipify — Internationalization (i18n) Required

Aipify is a global SaaS product. All user-facing text must use the i18n system from day one.

## Rules

1. **No hardcoded UI text** — never write strings directly in components, pages, or emails.
2. **Use translation keys** — always use `t("namespace.key")` or equivalent.
3. **Default language is English** — fallback to `en` when the user's locale is unsupported.
4. **Supported locales**: `en`, `no`, `sv`, `da` — new locales must be easy to add.
5. **Admin panel** uses the same translation system — no separate hardcoded admin strings.
6. **Email templates** must be multilingual — store under `locales/{locale}/emails/`.
7. **Mobile and desktop** share the same translation keys — no separate mobile-only strings.

## Locale structure

```text
locales/
├── en/
│   ├── common.json
│   ├── landing.json
│   ├── dashboard.json
│   ├── assistant.json
│   └── emails/
├── no/
├── sv/
└── da/
```

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<h1>Support Dashboard</h1>
<button>Save</button>

// ✅ GOOD
<h1>{t("dashboard.title")}</h1>
<button>{t("common.save")}</button>
```

## Future modules (all must follow i18n)

Support AI · Install AI · Analytics AI · Commerce AI · Assistant Chat · Notifications · Billing · Settings

## Technical debt

New text without i18n is technical debt and must be fixed before the feature is considered complete.
